    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "@EugeOrtiz This might be hidden under Developer-only settings. This would assist in debugging end-user connectivity issues - users would be able to see and send us their network stats/logs. Right now we can only get app crash dumps, and only when app crashed. Sometimes app seems to be healthy, but there are no data sent. So if an end-user experiences message delivery issues, they cannot really see what's going on.\r\n\r\nAll this info can be stored in logs, but a UI solution seems to be a nice option to have.\r\n\r\nThis is partially inspired by Apple Mail Connection Doctor (https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT204173)\n\n<blockquote><img src=\"//support.apple.com/library/content/dam/edam/applecare/images/en_US/social/open_graph_logo.png/\" width=\"48\" align=\"right\"><div>Apple Support</div><div><strong><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT204173\">Use Mail Connection Doctor</a></strong></div><div>Mail Connection Doctor can help explain why the Mail app isn't sending or receiving email on your Mac.\n</div></blockquote>",
